Assess survival in patients with HGG by CLK1 status

Ryan Corbett, Jo Lynne Rokita

2023

Purpose:

  • Generate survival models with CLK1 status (high vs. low) as covariate
  • Plot survival by CLK1 status

Setup

Packages and functions

load libraries and set directories

library(survival)
library(ggpubr)
library(tidyverse)
library('data.table')
library(patchwork)

# Set directories
root_dir <- rprojroot::find_root(rprojroot::has_dir(".git"))

Load histologies and subset for HGG and DMG

hgg_hist <- read_tsv(histologies_file) %>%
  dplyr::filter(Histology %in% c("DIPG or DMG", "Other high-grade glioma"),
                !is.na(OS_days) | !is.na(EFS_days)) %>%
  dplyr::select(Kids_First_Biospecimen_ID, Histology, mol_sub_group,
                OS_days, OS_years, OS_status,
                EFS_days, EFS_years, EFS_status)

Load rMATs file and subset for CLK1 exon 4 PSI values

splice_CLK1_df <-  fread(diff_psi_file) %>%
   dplyr::filter(geneSymbol=="CLK1",
                 exonStart_0base=="200860124", exonEnd=="200860215") %>%
  dplyr::rename('Kids_First_Biospecimen_ID'=sample_id,
                PSI = IncLevel1) %>%
  dplyr::select(Kids_First_Biospecimen_ID, PSI)

# join PSI value to hgg_hist
hgg_hist <- hgg_hist %>%
  left_join(splice_CLK1_df)
Joining with `by = join_by(Kids_First_Biospecimen_ID)`

Calculate CLK1 quantiles and define samples as Low, Medium, High within tumor histologies

quantiles_clk1_hgg <- quantile(hgg_hist$PSI[hgg_hist$Histology == "Other high-grade glioma"], probs=c(.25, .75), na.rm = TRUE)
lower_sbi_hgg <- quantiles_clk1_hgg[1]
upper_sbi_hgg <- quantiles_clk1_hgg[2]

quantiles_clk1_dmg <- quantile(hgg_hist$PSI[hgg_hist$Histology == "DIPG or DMG"], probs=c(.25, .75), na.rm = TRUE)
lower_sbi_dmg <- quantiles_clk1_dmg[1]
upper_sbi_dmg <- quantiles_clk1_dmg[2]

hgg_hist <- hgg_hist %>%
  mutate(clk1_status = case_when((Histology == "DIPG or DMG" & PSI > upper_sbi_dmg) |
                                  (Histology == "Other high-grade glioma" & PSI > upper_sbi_hgg) ~ "CLK1 exon 4 High",
                                 (Histology == "DIPG or DMG" & PSI <= lower_sbi_dmg) |
                                  (Histology == "Other high-grade glioma" & PSI <= lower_sbi_hgg) ~ "CLK1 exon 4 Low",
                                 TRUE ~ "Middle"))

Create survival df with only high & low CLK1 status, and relevel mol subgroups

survival_df <- hgg_hist %>%
  dplyr::filter(clk1_status %in% c("CLK1 exon 4 High", "CLK1 exon 4 Low")) %>%
  dplyr::mutate(mol_sub_group = fct_relevel(mol_sub_group,
                                            c("HGG, H3 wildtype", "HGG, H3 wildtype, TP53",
                                              "DHG, H3 G35", "DHG, H3 G35, TP53",
                                              "DMG, H3 K28", "DMG, H3 K28, TP53",
                                              "HGG, IDH, TP53", "HGG, PXA",
                                              "HGG, PXA, TP53", "IHG, NTRK-altered",
                                              "IHG, ROS1-altered")))

Generate KM models wiht clk1_status as variable

kap_os <- survival_analysis(
  metadata  = survival_df,
  ind_var = "clk1_status",
  test = "kap.meier",
  metadata_sample_col = "Kids_First_Biospecimen_ID",
  days_col = "OS_days",
  status_col = "OS_status"
)
Testing model: survival::Surv(OS_days, OS_status) ~ clk1_status with kap.meier
readr::write_rds(kap_os, file.path(results_dir,
                                   "logrank_HGG_OS_CLK1_status.RDS"))

kap_efs <- survival_analysis(
  metadata  = survival_df,
  ind_var = "clk1_status",
  test = "kap.meier",
  metadata_sample_col = "Kids_First_Biospecimen_ID",
  days_col = "EFS_days",
  status_col = "EFS_status"
)
Testing model: survival::Surv(EFS_days, EFS_status) ~ clk1_status with kap.meier
readr::write_rds(kap_efs, file.path(results_dir,
                                    "logrank_HGG_EFS_CLK1_status.RDS"))

Create KM plot

km_plot <- plotKM(model = list(kap_os, kap_efs),
                  variable = "clk1_status",
                  combined = T, 
                  title = "")
              
ggsave(file.path(plot_dir, "km_HGG_DMG_OS_EFS_CLK1_status.pdf"), km_plot,
       width = 10, height = 6, units = "in",
       device = "pdf")

There appears to be a subtype x clk1_status interaction effect, such that survival trends may differ in DMG vs. other HGG.
